{
  "name": "Triage Bot — Customer Support AI",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "updates": ["message"]
      },
      "id": "node-telegram-trigger",
      "name": "Telegram Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.telegramTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [0, 0],
      "credentials": {
        "telegramApi": {
          "id": "TELEGRAM_CREDENTIAL_ID",
          "name": "Telegram Bot"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "assignments": {
          "assignments": [
            {
              "id": "text",
              "name": "text",
              "value": "={{ $json.message.text }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "sender",
              "name": "sender",
              "value": "={{ $json.message.from.username || $json.message.from.first_name }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "sender_id",
              "name": "sender_id",
              "value": "={{ $json.message.from.id }}",
              "type": "number"
            },
            {
              "id": "chat_id",
              "name": "chat_id",
              "value": "={{ $json.message.chat.id }}",
              "type": "number"
            },
            {
              "id": "timestamp",
              "name": "timestamp",
              "value": "={{ new Date($json.message.date * 1000).toISOString() }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "received_at_ms",
              "name": "received_at_ms",
              "value": "={{ Date.now() }}",
              "type": "number"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "node-normalize",
      "name": "Normalize Input",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [220, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "combinator": "and"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.text }}",
              "rightValue": "",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "isNotEmpty"
              }
            },
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.text.length }}",
              "rightValue": 4000,
              "operator": {
                "type": "number",
                "operation": "lte"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "node-validate",
      "name": "Validate Input",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [440, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "type": "SystemMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": {
                "values": {
                  "string": "You are a customer support triage assistant. Your job is to analyze incoming customer messages and provide structured classification.\n\nFor each message, you must return a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n1. summary — A concise 1-2 sentence summary of the customer's issue in the same language as the original message.\n\n2. category — Exactly one of: \"billing\", \"technical_issue\", \"account_access\", \"feature_request\", \"complaint\", \"general_inquiry\"\n   - billing: payment, invoices, subscriptions, refunds, pricing\n   - technical_issue: bugs, errors, broken functionality, performance problems\n   - account_access: login problems, password reset, 2FA, account lockout\n   - feature_request: new feature suggestions, improvement ideas\n   - complaint: service quality complaints, negative experience, frustration about support\n   - general_inquiry: general questions, product info, documentation\n\n3. priority — One of: \"critical\", \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\"\n   - critical: service completely down for all users, data loss, security breach (passwords leaked, account hacked, unauthorized access detected). Use critical whenever the user mentions: hacking, data leak, passwords exposed, account compromised, database lost/empty, security incident.\n   - high: core functionality broken for this user, payment issues, account lockout\n   - medium: inconvenience with workaround, non-urgent billing questions\n   - low: ONLY for feature requests, general questions, documentation, pricing info. NEVER use low for complaints or access issues.\n\nCRITICAL RULE: If category = feature_request → priority MUST be low, always. Even if the user says urgent/blocking/critical — a feature that does not exist yet is always low priority for triage. Existing feature broken = technical_issue/high. Feature that does not exist yet = feature_request/low.\n\n4. confidence — A number between 0 and 1 indicating how confident you are in your classification. Lower confidence when:\n   - Message is ambiguous or could fit multiple categories\n   - Message is very short or lacks context\n   - Message contains multiple unrelated issues\n   - Emotional tone makes it hard to identify the core issue\n\n5. route — The team to route to, based on category:\n   - billing → \"Billing Team\"\n   - technical_issue → \"Engineering Support\"\n   - account_access → \"Account Security\"\n   - feature_request → \"Product Team\"\n   - complaint → \"Customer Success\"\n   - general_inquiry → \"General Support\"\n\nHere are examples of correct classifications:\n\nExample 1:\nMessage: Мне второй раз списали деньги за подписку в этом месяце. Верните деньги!\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"Клиенту дважды списали оплату за подписку, требует возврат\", \"category\": \"billing\", \"priority\": \"high\", \"confidence\": 0.95, \"route\": \"Billing Team\"}\n\nExample 2:\nMessage: The dashboard keeps showing a blank page after the latest update. I tried clearing cache and different browsers.\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"Dashboard shows blank page after update, persists across browsers and cache clearing\", \"category\": \"technical_issue\", \"priority\": \"high\", \"confidence\": 0.92, \"route\": \"Engineering Support\"}\n\nExample 3:\nMessage: Can you add dark mode?\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"User requests dark mode feature\", \"category\": \"feature_request\", \"priority\": \"low\", \"confidence\": 0.95, \"route\": \"Product Team\"}\n\nExample 4:\nMessage: I cannot log in and I also got charged twice\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"User has both login issues and double billing charge\", \"category\": \"account_access\", \"priority\": \"high\", \"confidence\": 0.6, \"route\": \"Account Security\"}\n\nExample 5:\nMessage: Все пароли утекли в интернет\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"Пользователь сообщает об утечке всех паролей — критический security инцидент\", \"category\": \"account_access\", \"priority\": \"critical\", \"confidence\": 0.95, \"route\": \"Account Security\"}\n\nExample 6:\nMessage: Can you add an export to Excel feature to the reports page?\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"User requests Excel export functionality for reports\", \"category\": \"feature_request\", \"priority\": \"low\", \"confidence\": 0.97, \"route\": \"Product Team\"}\n\nExample 7:\nMessage: We urgently need API access for automation — this is blocking our entire engineering team\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"Team requests API access feature for automation workflows\", \"category\": \"feature_request\", \"priority\": \"low\", \"confidence\": 0.88, \"route\": \"Product Team\"}\n\nExample 8:\nMessage: Your support takes 3 days to respond. This is unacceptable.\nResponse: {\"summary\": \"User complains about slow support response time\", \"category\": \"complaint\", \"priority\": \"medium\", \"confidence\": 0.93, \"route\": \"Customer Success\"}\n\nNow classify the following message. Respond ONLY with valid JSON. No explanations, no markdown formatting."
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": {
          "values": {
            "string": "={{ $json.text }}"
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "node-deepseek-chain",
      "name": "DeepSeek — Classify",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.4,
      "position": [660, -60],
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "maxTries": 3,
      "waitBetweenTries": 2000
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": "deepseek-chat",
        "options": {
          "maxTokens": 300,
          "temperature": 0
        }
      },
      "id": "node-deepseek-model",
      "name": "DeepSeek Chat Model",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatDeepSeek",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [660, 80],
      "credentials": {
        "deepSeekApi": {
          "id": "DEEPSEEK_CREDENTIAL_ID",
          "name": "DeepSeek API"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "assignments": {
          "assignments": [
            {
              "id": "parsed",
              "name": "parsed",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text) }}",
              "type": "object"
            },
            {
              "id": "summary",
              "name": "summary",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text).summary }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "category",
              "name": "category",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text).category }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "priority",
              "name": "priority",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text).priority }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "confidence",
              "name": "confidence",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text).confidence }}",
              "type": "number"
            },
            {
              "id": "route",
              "name": "route",
              "value": "={{ JSON.parse($json.text).route }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "processing_time_ms",
              "name": "processing_time_ms",
              "value": "={{ Date.now() - $('Normalize Input').item.json.received_at_ms }}",
              "type": "number"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "node-parse",
      "name": "Parse Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [880, -60],
      "onError": "continueErrorOutput"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "assignments": {
          "assignments": [
            {
              "id": "valid_category",
              "name": "category",
              "value": "={{ ['billing','technical_issue','account_access','feature_request','complaint','general_inquiry'].includes($json.category) ? $json.category : 'general_inquiry' }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "valid_priority",
              "name": "priority",
              "value": "={{ ['critical','high','medium','low'].includes($json.priority) ? $json.priority : 'medium' }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "valid_confidence",
              "name": "confidence",
              "value": "={{ (typeof $json.confidence === 'number' && $json.confidence >= 0 && $json.confidence <= 1) ? $json.confidence : 0.5 }}",
              "type": "number"
            }
          ]
        },
        "includeOtherFields": true
      },
      "id": "node-validate-output",
      "name": "Validate AI Output",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [1100, -60]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "combinator": "or"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.priority }}",
              "rightValue": "critical",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "equals"
              }
            },
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.confidence }}",
              "rightValue": 0.8,
              "operator": {
                "type": "number",
                "operation": "lt"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "node-confidence-check",
      "name": "Needs Review?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1320, -60],
      "notes": "Human review если: confidence < 0.8 ИЛИ priority = critical (всегда human review для critical)"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "append",
        "documentId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "mode": "id",
          "value": "1X-6Cv2KBBxP0YqQJLmlf4wcUvuIL56qNT1uxWMcSttE"
        },
        "sheetName": {
          "__rl": true,
          "mode": "name",
          "value": "Triage Log"
        },
        "columns": {
          "mappingMode": "defineBelow",
          "value": {
            "timestamp": "={{ $('Normalize Input').item.json.timestamp }}",
            "sender": "={{ $('Normalize Input').item.json.sender }}",
            "original_message": "={{ $('Normalize Input').item.json.text }}",
            "summary": "={{ $json.summary }}",
            "category": "={{ $json.category }}",
            "priority": "={{ $json.priority }}",
            "confidence": "={{ $json.confidence }}",
            "route": "={{ $json.route }}",
            "needs_review": "false",
            "reviewer_decision": "",
            "final_category": "={{ $json.category }}",
            "processing_time_ms": "={{ $json.processing_time_ms }}"
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "node-sheets-auto",
      "name": "Google Sheets — Auto Route",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets",
      "typeVersion": 4.5,
      "position": [1580, -160],
      "credentials": {
        "googleSheetsOAuth2Api": {
          "id": "GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIAL_ID",
          "name": "Google Sheets"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "append",
        "documentId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "mode": "id",
          "value": "1X-6Cv2KBBxP0YqQJLmlf4wcUvuIL56qNT1uxWMcSttE"
        },
        "sheetName": {
          "__rl": true,
          "mode": "name",
          "value": "Triage Log"
        },
        "columns": {
